"Damn it, they managed to tame a fully grown sandworm?" The leader of the
 mercenaries whined.
 "That's going to be a nightmare to fight."

\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Simulacrum number one had to agree.
 Although he could easily detect incoming sandworm attacks due to his mind
 sense, it was hard to deal with attacks that came from underground.
 Especially since the sandworm was huge, meaning they had little chance of
 stopping its attacks and could only move out of the way whenever they detected
 it coming.

\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"I have an idea," Zach-simulacrum said, quickly performing an alteration spell
 that hardened the sand beneath them into a stone platform and then raising it
 high into the sky.

\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"There," Zach-simulacrum said, smiling.
