 dog trying to dry itself off, and a series of translucent, glowing, yellow
 wings grew out of its sides.
 They were long and paper-thin, reminiscent of dragonfly wings, and looked
 comically inappropriate for lifting a creature like that into the air… but as
 the creature's many golden wings started slowly undulating like oars on a
 boat, the sandworm slowly lifted itself into the sky and then reoriented
 itself towards them.

\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Zach-simulacrum immediately deflated.

\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
"Now this just isn't fair," he complained.

\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Simulacrum number one looked at the flying sandworm, which was currently flying
 towards them while accompanied by a swarm of devil wasps and decided he
 couldn't agree more.

\end_layout

