Zorian turned to Alanic walking next to them, who was ignoring their banter in
 favor of scanning the walls for some reason.
 Probably looking for some clues as to where they are – all of the walls still
 retained detailed carvings of various religious scenes.
 Most of them were from Ikosian era, but some of them had been crudely
 'repurposed' by the sulrothum, who did their best to modify the carvings into
 something that fitted better with their own religious beliefs.
 Alanic was very unamused by their efforts, if his deepening frown was of any
 indication.

